</taxonomicName>
], two of which also occur in South African waters: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[241,389,1365,1388]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="excentrica">
<emphasis box="[241,389,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. excentrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ridley" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[448,603,1364,1389]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="vagabunda">
<emphasis box="[448,603,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. vagabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A third species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[810,936,1365,1388]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[810,936,1365,1388]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carter" box="[1161,1316,1364,1388]" firstAuthor="Carter" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="101 - 120" refId="ref42136" refString="Carter, H. J. (1882) Contributions to our knowledge of the Spongida. Order II. Ceratina. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 5, 8, 101 - 120, pl. IX." type="journal article" year="1882">Carter (1882)</bibRefCitation>
from Port Elizabeth on the south coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[502,650,1399,1424]" name="South Africa" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,463,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authority="(Burton, 1931)" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1931" baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[199,676,1436,1461]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="excentrica">
<emphasis box="[199,501,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Spheciospongia excentrica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Burton" box="[517,668,1436,1460]" firstAuthor="Burton" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="337 - 358" refId="ref41703" refString="Burton, M. (1931) On a collection of marine sponges mostly from the Natal coast. Annals of the Natal Museum, 6 (3), 337 - 358." type="journal article" year="1931">Burton, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is a non-stipitate cup-shaped sponge possessing centrotylote oxeas and tylotes and no spirasters, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[582,734,1471,1496]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[582,734,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[741,831,1471,1496]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[741,831,1471,1496]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is massive, vase-shaped with numerous spirasters but no centrotylote oxeas present. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[492,794,1508,1533]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="excentrica">
<emphasis box="[492,794,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Spheciospongia excentrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has smaller tylostyles (
<quantity box="[1057,1145,1508,1532]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="320.0">320 µm</quantity>
) oppose to those found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,304,1543,1568]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,304,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[313,405,1543,1568]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[313,405,1543,1568]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pulitzer-Finali's" box="[414,678,1543,1568]" firstAuthor="Pulitzer-Finali's" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="247 - 350" refId="ref48016" refString="Pulitzer-Finali, G. (1993) A collection of marine sponges from East Africa. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale G. Doria' 89, RAHIM, M. A. 1979. Porifera. Publications Saudi Biological Society, 3 (46), 247 - 350" type="journal article" year="1993">Pulitzer-Finali’s (1993)</bibRefCitation>
description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[854,1001,1544,1568]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="excentrica">
<emphasis box="[854,1001,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. excentrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1074,1184,1543,1568]" name="Kenya" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Mombasa</collectingCountry>
differs from 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton's" firstAuthor="Burton's" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="337 - 358" refId="ref41703" refString="Burton, M. (1931) On a collection of marine sponges mostly from the Natal coast. Annals of the Natal Museum, 6 (3), 337 - 358." type="journal article" year="1931">Burton’s (1931)</bibRefCitation>
<typeStatus box="[233,281,1581,1605]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
in being stipitate, have spirasters (although only two recorded) and smaller tylostyles, (
<quantity box="[1275,1424,1580,1605]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="360.0" valueMax="460.0" valueMin="260.0">260–460 µm</quantity>
). Whether Pulitzer-Finali’s species from 
<collectingCountry box="[590,700,1615,1640]" name="Kenya" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Mombasa</collectingCountry>
is 
<taxonomicName box="[733,865,1616,1640]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="exentrica">
<emphasis box="[733,865,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. exentrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is questionable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,463,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lendenfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[199,460,1652,1677]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="florida">
<emphasis box="[199,460,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Spheciospongia florida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[645,745,1652,1677]" name="Tanzania" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Zanzibar</collectingCountry>
and widely distributed within the WIO, is columnar in shape and differs in spiculation and spicule dimensions to 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[744,896,1687,1712]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[744,896,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[905,996,1687,1712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[905,996,1687,1712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ridley" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1052,1207,1687,1712]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="vagabunda">
<emphasis box="[1052,1207,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. vagabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lendenfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1224,1329,1687,1712]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="florida">
<emphasis box="[1224,1329,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. florida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,1687,1712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[151,299,1724,1749]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="425.0" valueMax="650.0" valueMin="200.0">200–650 µm</quantity>
&amp; spirasters 
<quantity box="[464,574,1724,1749]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="5.0">5–15 µm</quantity>
; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ridley" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[591,749,1724,1749]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="vagabunda">
<emphasis box="[591,749,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. vagabunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[761,859,1724,1749]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
tylostyles 600 
<date box="[1046,1101,1724,1748]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1920-10">
x 
<quantity box="[1073,1101,1724,1748]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="20.0">20</quantity>
</date>
µm &amp; spirasters 
<quantity box="[1316,1398,1724,1749]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="32.0">32 µm</quantity>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[281,370,1759,1784]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[281,370,1759,1784]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
tylostyles, 
<quantity box="[498,640,1760,1784]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.485" metricValueMax="4.99" metricValueMin="3.9799999999999995" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="448.5" valueMax="499.0" valueMin="398.0">398–499 µm</quantity>
&amp; spirasters 
<quantity box="[789,906,1760,1784]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="18.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="17.0">17–19 µm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,463,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carter" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[207,488,1796,1821]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis box="[207,488,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Spheciospongia capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[640,792,1796,1821]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[640,792,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[800,891,1796,1821]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[800,891,1796,1821]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in being semicircular, flat and having contorted spirasters with four bends as oppose to being c-shaped as in the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,463,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,510,1868,1893]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,510,1868,1893]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Spheciospongia ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[520,614,1868,1893]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[520,614,1868,1893]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has long thin c-shaped spirasters with spines only on the outer curve, sinuous tylostyles and styles, and the tylostyles project through the ectosome. The presence of subdermal cavities within the choanosome, a paratangential reticulation of tylostyles and a confused reticulation of tylostyles in the choanosome have not been observed in 
<emphasis box="[596,1066,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burton" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[596,743,1977,2000]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="excentrica">S. excentrica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lendenfeld" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[755,859,1976,2001]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="florida">S. florida</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dendy" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[915,1062,1976,2001]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="globularis">S. globularis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This may be a diagnostic feature of 
<taxonomicName authority="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson, 2019" authorityName="Samaai &amp; Pillay &amp; Janson" authorityYear="2019" box="[181,332,2012,2037]" class="Demospongiae" family="Clionaidae" genus="Spheciospongia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="ndabazithe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[181,332,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S. ndabazithe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[339,428,2012,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[339,422,2012,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2651460/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" startId="19.[151,250,1985,2007]" targetBox="[200,1387,193,1964]" targetPageId="19">
